# Growth checklist maintenance

After completing any growth-related task, update the **## Growth** checklist in `README.md` in the same edit session.

## What triggers an update

- Adding, renaming, or removing files under `growth/` (drafts, templates, playbooks, grant applications)
- Setting up or changing social channel accounts (X, Discord, Telegram, etc.)
- Publishing content (blog posts, tweets, LinkedIn posts, Substack issues, YouTube videos, podcast pitches, Farcaster casts)
- Creating or completing lead magnets, VSL, or other Layer 2 capture assets
- Configuring or changing Layer 3 nurture tooling (email platform, sequences, lead scoring)
- Setting up or modifying VC pipeline tooling (Clay, Instantly, Expandi, Docsend, etc.)
- Submitting or updating grant applications

## What to do

- **Check off** items that are now complete (`- [ ]` → `- [x]`).
- **Add new items** when a growth workstream or deliverable is introduced that is not yet tracked.
- **Remove or reword** items that are no longer relevant due to strategy changes.
- Keep items grouped under the correct subheading (Content Infrastructure, Social Channels, Content Production, Lead Capture, Lead Management, VC Pipeline, Grants).

## What to skip

- Do not update the checklist for typo-only or formatting-only edits to growth files.
- Do not duplicate information already captured by a CHANGELOG entry in the same session.
